  "body": "As per conversation in discord:\r\n\r\n> I would like to put the check in the RPC daemon so it returns an error if the node is still out of sync.\r\n\r\nCurrently, RPC daemon returns `0x0` for request to `eth_blockNumber` during initial sync (no indication that it cannot return a valid value because there is no valid value). This may be desired result. We should do what other nodes (such as `geth`) do.\r\n\r\nIt would be interesting to test other RPC commands during initial syncing to see if any of them return 'non-sense' data and if they should instead return an error or a warning.",
